a1Installation.name: a1Installation
a1Installation.description: The time and date when this component was installed.

a1Verify.name: a1Verify
a1Verify.description: A code that provides a level of verification that the component is stillinstalled and working.

tUpsBattery.name: tUpsBattery
tUpsBattery.description: The UPS Battery group contains information regarding the UPSsystem's battery status.

a2BatteryStatus.name: a2BatteryStatus
a2BatteryStatus.description: The indication of the capacity remaining in the UPS system's batteries. Avalue of 'battery normal' indicates that the remaining estimated minutes of run-time isgreater than the UPS's configured 'low battery time' (typically two minutes). A valueof 'battery low' indicates that the remaining estimated minutes of battery run-time isless than or equal to the UPS's configur d 'low battery time'. A value of 'batterydepleted' indicates that the UPS will be unable to sustain the present load when and ifthe uti

a2SecondsOnBattery.name: a2SecondsOnBattery
a2SecondsOnBattery.description: If the UPS is on battery power, the elapsed time in seconds since theUPS last switched to battery power, or the time since the UPS component software waslast restarted, whichever is less. Zero shall be returned if the UPS is not on batterypower.

a2EstimatedMinutesRemaining.name: a2EstimatedMinutesRemaining
a2EstimatedMinutesRemaining.description: An estimate in minutes of the time to battery charge depletion under thepresent load conditions if the utility power is off and remains off, or if it were to be lostand remain off.

a2EstimatedChargeRemaining.name: a2EstimatedChargeRemaining
a2EstimatedChargeRemaining.description: An estimate of the time to battery charge depletion under the present load conditions if theutility power is off and remains off, or if it were to be lost and remain off. The valuerepresents a percent of full charge.

a2BatteryVoltage.name: a2BatteryVoltage
a2BatteryVoltage.description: The magnitude of the present battery voltage in 0.1 volts DC.

a2BatteryCurrent.name: a2BatteryCurrent
a2BatteryCurrent.description: The present battery current in 0.1 Amps DC.

a2TemperatureProbeIndex.name: a2TemperatureProbeIndex
a2TemperatureProbeIndex.description: Index into the Temperature Probe table. This probe indicates the ambienttemperature at or near the UPS battery casing.

a2FruGroupIndex.name: a2FruGroupIndex
a2FruGroupIndex.description: If this is a Field Replaceable Unit or it is part of another FRU, this providesan index into the FRU table; 'value = -1' indicates that the group is not a FRU.

a2OperationalGroupIndex.name: a2OperationalGroupIndex
a2OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State table for this device.

tTemperatureProbe.name: tTemperatureProbe
tTemperatureProbe.description: This group defines the attributes for the temperature probes in thissystem.

a3TemperatureProbeTableIndex.name: a3TemperatureProbeTableIndex
a3TemperatureProbeTableIndex.description: Index into this temperature probe table.

a3TemperatureProbeLocation.name: a3TemperatureProbeLocation
a3TemperatureProbeLocation.description: Identifies the physical location of the temperature probe.

a3TemperatureProbeDescription.name: a3TemperatureProbeDescription
a3TemperatureProbeDescription.description: Additional descriptive information about the temperature probe orprobe's location.

a3TemperatureStatus.name: a3TemperatureStatus
a3TemperatureStatus.description: Defines the status of the temperature monitored by this temperat reprobe.

a3TemperatureProbeTemperatureReading.name: a3TemperatureProbeTemperatureReading
a3TemperatureProbeTemperatureReading.description: The present temperature reading of this temperature probe in 1/10th degrees C. 0x8000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3MonitoredTemperatureNominalReading.name: a3MonitoredTemperatureNominalReading
a3MonitoredTemperatureNominalReading.description: The nominal temperature reading of the temperature monitored by this probe in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'

a3MonitoredTemperatureNormalMaximum.name: a3MonitoredTemperatureNormalMaximum
a3MonitoredTemperatureNormalMaximum.description: The normal maximum temperature reading of the temperature monitored by this probe in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3MonitoredTemperatureNormalMinimum.name: a3MonitoredTemperatureNormalMinimum
a3MonitoredTemperatureNormalMinimum.description: The normal minimum temperature reading of the temperature monitored by this probe in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3TemperatureProbeMaximum.name: a3TemperatureProbeMaximum
a3TemperatureProbeMaximum.description: The maximum temperature reading specified to be readable by this probe in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'

a3TemperatureProbeMinimum.name: a3TemperatureProbeMinimum
a3TemperatureProbeMinimum.description: The minimum temperature reading specified to be readable by this probe in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'

a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Non_c.name: a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Non_c
a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Non_c.description: The lower non-critical threshold for the temperature reading set by the user, in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupport d'.

a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Non_c.name: a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Non_c
a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Non_c.description: The upper non-critical threshold for the temperature probe, in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Criti.name: a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Criti
a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Criti.description: The lower critical threshold for the temperature probe, in 1/10 degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Criti.name: a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Criti
a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Criti.description: The upper critical threshold for the temperature probe, in /10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Non_r.name: a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Non_r
a3TemperatureReadingLowerThreshold_Non_r.description: The lower non-recoverable threshold for the temperature probe, in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Non_r.name: a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Non_r
a3TemperatureReadingUpperThreshold_Non_r.description: The upper non-recoverable threshold for the temperature probe, in 1/10th degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3TemperatureProbeResolution.name: a3TemperatureProbeResolution
a3TemperatureProbeResolution.description: The resolution for the reading from this temperature probe, in tenths of 1/10th degrees C. '0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3TemperatureProbeTolerance.name: a3TemperatureProbeTolerance
a3TemperatureProbeTolerance.description: The tolerance for the reading from this temperature probe, in plus/minus 1/10 degrees C. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsupported'.

a3TemperatureProbeAccuracy.name: a3TemperatureProbeAccuracy
a3TemperatureProbeAccuracy.description: The accuracy for the reading from this temperature probe, in plus/minus hundredths of a percent. 0x80000000 denotes 'unknown' or 'unsuppor ed'.

a3FruGroupIndex.name: a3FruGroupIndex
a3FruGroupIndex.description: Index into the FRU table. A value of -1 indicates that this device is not an FRU.

a3OperationalGroupIndex.name: a3OperationalGroupIndex
a3OperationalGroupIndex.description: Index into the Operational State table

a4OperationalStateInstanceIndex.description: The Index into the Operational State table.

a4DeviceGroupIndex.name: a4DeviceGroupIndex
a4DeviceGroupIndex.description: The group ID of the group referencing this instance.

a4OperationalStatus.name: a4OperationalStatus
a4OperationalStatus.description: The operational status of the Device Group instance.

a4UsageState.name: a4UsageState
a4UsageState.description: The usage state of the Device Group instance.

a4AvailabilityStatus.name: a4AvailabilityStatus
a4AvailabilityStatus.description: The availability status of the Device Group instance.

a4AdministrativeState.name: a4AdministrativeState
a4AdministrativeState.description: The administrative state of the Device Group instance.

a4FatalErrorCount.name: a4FatalErrorCount
a4FatalErrorCount.description: The accumulated Fatal or Non-recoverable error count for this DeviceGroup instance.

a4MajorErrorCount.name: a4MajorErrorCount
a4MajorErrorCount.description: The accumulated Major or Critical error count for this Device Groupinstance.

a4WarningErrorCount.name: a4WarningErrorCount
a4WarningErrorCount.description: The accumulated Warning or Non-Critical error count for this DeviceGroup instance.

a4CurrentErrorStatus.name: a4CurrentErrorStatus
a4CurrentErrorStatus.description: This attribute presents the current error status for this Device Groupinstance. The most critical error status in effect should be presented. I.e. if a part of theDevice Group instance is 'Critical', while other status is 'Non-critical' then the status'Critical' should be reported.

tDiagnostics.name: tDiagnostics
tDiagnostics.description: This group defines the diagnostic functions that are provided by thiscomponent for analyzing potential failures within the component. A diagnosticfunction could be an actual test run against the component, the results of a self-test ofthe component, an analysis of failure information captured during a failure of thecomponent, or an analysis of the current state of the component.

a5DiagnosticFunctionTableIndex.name: a5DiagnosticFunctionTableIndex
a5DiagnosticFunctionTableIndex.description: A unique identifier for this specific diagnostic function.

a5DiagnosticFunctionName.name: a5DiagnosticFunctionName
a5DiagnosticFunctionName.description: A specific descriptive name of the diagnostic function, includin versioninformation, if relevant.

a5DiagnosticFunctionDescription.name: a5DiagnosticFunctionDescription
a5DiagnosticFunctionDescription.description: A description of what this diagnostic function does.

a5ExclusiveAccessRequired.name: a5ExclusiveAccessRequired
a5ExclusiveAccessRequired.description: Indicates whether this diagnostic function requires exclusive access tothe device or component, implying that the user or management applicati n must takesome action within the operating system to ensure that the device or component cannotbe used by any other function.

a5PrerequisiteConditions.name: a5PrerequisiteConditions
a5PrerequisiteConditions.description: Indicates what conditions must be met before this diagnostic functioncan be run.

a5PrerequisiteDiagnosticFunction.name: a5PrerequisiteDiagnosticFunction
a5PrerequisiteDiagnosticFunction.description: If non-0, this specifies the ID of another diagnostic function that must berun immediately prior to this one.

tDiagnosticRequestGroup.name: tDiagnosticRequestGroup
tDiagnosticRequestGroup.description: This group defines the attributes which a management application usesto request an actual diagnostic analysis.

a6DiagnosticFunctionReserveKey.name: a6DiagnosticFunctionReserveKey
a6DiagnosticFunctionReserveKey.description: Indicates whether the interface to this component's diagnostic functionsis reserved. A zero value returned on a get indicates that a reserve is already in effect. A non-zero value indicates that no reserve was in effect, and the returned value may beused as a reserve key.

a6DiagnosticFunctionRequest.name: a6DiagnosticFunctionRequest
a6DiagnosticFunctionRequest.description: The ID of the specific diagnostic function which is being requested. Ifthe interface is reserved, a set request to this attribute should also set the DiagnosticFunction Reserve Key with the reserve key value.

a6DiagnosticFunctionResult.name: a6DiagnosticFunctionResult
a6DiagnosticFunctionResult.description: The integer-based result code of the last diagnostic function run.

tDiagnosticResults.name: tDiagnosticResults
tDiagnosticResults.description: This group defines the attributes for interpreting diagnostic functionresult codes.

a7DiagnosticFunctionId.name: a7DiagnosticFunctionId
a7DiagnosticFunctionId.description: The unique ID for a specific diagnostic function.

a7DiagnosticFunctionResult.name: a7DiagnosticFunctionResult
a7DiagnosticFunctionResult.description: An integer-based result code of the diagnostic function.

a7DiagnosticFunctionResultDescription.name: a7DiagnosticFunctionResultDescription
a7DiagnosticFunctionResultDescription.description: A description of what this result code for this diagnostic functionmeans, including suggested corrective actions, where possible.

a7FaultIsolatedToThisComponent.name: a7FaultIsolatedToThisComponent
a7FaultIsolatedToThisComponent.description: An indicator of whether the fault is strictly isolated within the bounds ofthis component. A False value indicates that the fault might be caused by a failingparent component; for example, a disk test may fail because of a faulty disk controller.

tErrorControlGroup.name: tErrorControlGroup
tErrorControlGroup.description: Indication control and status for the parent group.

a8Selfid.name: a8Selfid
a8Selfid.description: Instance id. A unique number that identifies this row.

a8NumberOfFatalErrors.name: a8NumberOfFatalErrors
a8NumberOfFatalErrors.description: Count of all fatal errors since system startup.

a8NumberOfMajorErrors.name: a8NumberOfMajorErrors
a8NumberOfMajorErrors.description: Count of all major errors since system startup.

a8NumberOfWarnings.name: a8NumberOfWarnings
a8NumberOfWarnings.description: Count of all warning errors since system startup.

a8ErrorStatusType.name: a8ErrorStatusType
a8ErrorStatusType.description: Indicates the type of detection that set the current error status.
